e: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Winnington was born in 1365, in Delves, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard De Wynnington, was 20 and his mother, Emma de Mainwaring, was 14. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Catherine Holland. He died in 1435, in Winnington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1365–1435":"1365–1435","1367–1417":"1367–1417","1370–1427":"1370–1427","1372–Female":"1372–Surnud","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1400–1441":"1400–1441","1445–Female":"1445–Surnud","1345–1422":"1345–1422","1352–1402":"1352–1402","before 1365":"enne 1365","1352":"1352","1374":"1374","1372":"1372","Abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1370":"1370","1380":"1380","1402":"1402","1435":"1435","1445":"1445","1422":"1422","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1367":"1367","1365":"1365","1430":"1430","1441":"1441","1417":"1417","1427":"1427","Delves, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Delves, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Winnington, Cheshire, England":"Winnington, Cheshire, England","Winnington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Winnington, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Winnington Hall, Northwich, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Northwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1365–1435":"1365–1435","1367–1417":"1367–1417","1370–1427":"1370–1427","1372–Female":"1372–Kuollut","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","1380–1430":"1380–1430","1400–1441":"1400–1441","1445–Female":"1445–Kuollut","1345